title: Fall Out Boy announces 'Wintour' tour including date in Syracuse | syracuse.com
text:
Rock band Fall Out Boy has announced dates for a winter tour, dubbed "Wintour." The tour includes a stop in Syracuse next year.
Fall Out Boy will perform at the War Memorial Arena at the Oncenter on Sunday, March 6, 2016.
Wintour poster Chris Baker | cbaker@syracuse.com Ticket prices for the Syracuse show have not been announced. Tickets will go on sale Friday, Oct. 16 at noon via Ticketmaster.com , by phone at 800-745-3000 or in person at the Solvay Bank Box Office at the Oncenter (760 S. State St.) The rock band from the Chicago area took a hiatus in 2010 following a successful decade that included the hit song "Sugar, We're Going Down" and a Grammy nomination. They reunited in 2012 and have since released two albums, including this year's "American Beauty/American Psycho."
Wintour includes 20 cities and will feature Awolnation and Pvris as openers.
An an apparent nod to the popular HBO series "Game of Thrones," the band used the slogan "Wintour is Coming" to tease the tour. A concert poster features cartoons of the four band members carrying swords and battle axes.
Fall Out Boy performed at the grandstand at the NYS Fair in 2013. Playing through a rain storm, the band drew a crowd of just more than 3,700.
